URN:CornellLabOfOrnithology:EBIRD:OBS438570945	2016-10-25 21:03:52	10817	species	Ladder-backed Woodpecker	Dryobates scalaris			1				United States	US	Nevada	US-NV	Clark	US-NV-003		33			Spring Mountain Ranch SP	L337028	H	36.0690146	-115.4588759	2016-10-25	08:55:00	obsr221195	S32232203	Traveling	P22	EBIRD	155	3.219		1	1		0	1	0		I attempted to repeat Alvaro Jaramillo's Philadelphia Vireo sighting but to no avail.  The reported site is up the canyon from Harriet Lake where several large pipes cross underneath the road.  Lot of potential habitat for it to be in if it is still here.   Weather was interesting with cloudy / semi-foggy conditions at the beginning and eventually clearing to partly cloudy.  Temps approx high 50's to mid+ 60's with slight to modest breeze.   More species than I expected but had to work the area pretty hard to find what I did.  Also saw what was probably a Greater Spreadwing Damselfly at the vireo site for those who follow Odes.  Lastly, lots of Monarch Butterflies as it warmed up, perhaps as many as 10.
